<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[const validateNumber = n => !isNaN(parseFloat(n)) && isFinite(n) && Number(n) == n;]]></content>
	<description>Returns `true` if the given value is a number, `false` otherwise.  Use `!isNaN` in combination with `parseFloat()` to check if the argument is a number. Use `isFinite()` to check if the number is finite. Use `Number()` to check if the coercion holds.</description>
	<tabTrigger>validateNumber</tabTrigger>
	<scope>source.js</scope>
</snippet>